Name: Glow Inner Beauty Essential Powder
Short description: A daily beauty powder containing prebiotics, probiotics with an array of nutrient superfoods to support a healthy gut and promote radiant hydrated skin.  Now, with a supercharged formula.
Description:
A daily beauty powder for radiant skin and gut health, now with a supercharged formula.  The Glow inner beauty contains  18 Certified Organic wholefoods including bio-fermented maqui berries, queen garnet plum and pomegranate fruit peel extract, vitamin C to help boost collagen production and zinc to support healthy hair and nails. Plus provitamin A, broad-spectrum B vitamins and more probiotics and postbiotics^ thanks to our more potent fermentation process, this berry-flavoured blend promotes luminous skin from the inside out. Containing more antioxidants, polyphenols and phytonutrients, this nutrient-dense powder supports glowing skin, gut health and overall well-being. Now with double the provitamin A  from natural sources including the microalgae Dunaliella Salina, which is necessary for the cellular turnover process and contributes to healthy immune system function, and extra vitamin C  for collagen formation. Plus naturally occurring B vitamins derived from sprouted quinoa, including biotin, which contributes to the maintenance of healthy hair and skin, helps with macronutrient metabolism and energy production, and activated niacinamide (vitamin B3) which is integral for normal skin function and structure, energy release from food and helps with the reduction of tiredness and fatigue. Supercharged using our unique Flora Culture bio-fermentation process, GLOW contains a natural broad-spectrum probiotic, prebiotics and postbiotics to feed the beneficial bacteria in your gut because a healthy microbiome means healthy , hydrated and radiant skin. Features & Benefits of The Beauty Chef Glow inner beauty essential powder
  • hydrated & radiant skin
  • improved gut health
  • FODMAP friendly
  • contains prebiotics which is the food that feeds probiotics in one formulation
  • Vegan, Certified Organic, microbiologist-approved, cruelty free
  • non GMO
  • no artificial flavours, preservatives or colours
  • no added gluten, dairy, soy, eggs or nuts.
Tags: cruelty free, vegan

Meta: how_to:
Mix 1 tsp (5g) in 200mL of water, a smoothie, yoghurt or your favourite drink and consume immediately. For optimal results, GLOW should be consumed daily in chilled or room temperature beverages and can be taken with any other Beauty Chef product.

Inner Beauty Essentials are designed to be amplified with a Boost—COLLAGEN, HYDRATION, ANTIOXIDANT or OMEGA ELIXIR™. 

Storage: Refrigerate after opening and use within 90 days. Always use a dry spoon.

Description:
The Beauty Chef's Sleep Inner Beauty Powder is a  nighttime tonic that helps reduce sleeplessness and relieves mild anxiety symptoms while boosting antioxidant activity and nourishing your gut and skin health. As the name suggests, Sleep is scientifically formulated to soothe your nerves and deepen your sleep. The formula contains natural sedatives, passionflower and lemon balm, alongside sour cherry - naturally rich in the sleep-giving hormone, melatonin. With bio-fermented pawpaw leaf and turmeric root and 1.5 billion probiotics per serve, the formula is supercharged by The Beauty Chef's exclusive Flora Culture  fermentation process, for greater potency and absorption. When you sleep, your body is hard at work creating growth hormones which play an important role in cell regeneration and repair, and the maintenance of good health. Antioxidant activities are also increased and this helps combat the damaging effects of oxidative stress created throughout the day, by exposure to the sun and environmental pollutants.   Features & benefits of Sleep inner beauty powder:
  • good for anyone with trouble sleeping
  • A therapeutic medicine listed with Therapeutic goods administration (TGA)
  • Promotes a good night's sleep

  • Fights premature ageing
  • Helps restore good gut health

Name: Vanilla Body Inner Beauty Powder
Short description: A bio-fermented protein powder, super-food supplement, prebiotic, probiotic and metabolism booster, all conveniently rolled into one award-winning, multi-tasking formula.
Description:
For: Anyone looking for a nutritious, protein-rich superfood powder to kick-start metabolism and help bring the body back into balance. Bring your body back into balance with The Beauty Chef's Body Inner Beauty Powder, a revolutionary bio-fermented protein powder, super-food supplement, prebiotic, probiotic and metabolism booster, all conveniently rolled into one award-winning, multi-tasking formula. With over 40 Certified Organic ingredients, Body Inner Beauty Powder is designed as a healthy snack or meal supplement to help boost nutrition, immunity and/or achieve or maintain a healthy weight range. A powerful all-round formula to help improve energy levels and general wellbeing. The nutrient-dense, vegan formula is packed with four clean sources of bio-available organic plant protein, important for building and maintaining healthy tissue and muscle, maintaining metabolic efficiency, keeping blood sugar levels balanced and keeping you feeling fuller longer. The perfect, well balanced snack,this powder   is also rich in bio-fermented super-fruits, vegetables, leafy greens, probiotics, prebiotics and matcha green tea, making it a great source of fibre, antioxidants, vitamins and minerals,including 100% of the RDI of vitamin C and 50% of the RDI of vitamin D. The ingredients in the Body Inner Beauty Powder have been bio-fermented using The Beauty Chef's exclusive Flora Culture fermentation process to increase the bio-availability of the nutrients and create a live, broad-spectrum probiotic for a beautiful belly. This powerful formula, available in both real Vanilla and Chocolate, is a delicious way to help re-balance your body weight or simply improve your health with a powerful blend of easily digested, nutrient-dense wholefoods. Benefits:
  • Boosts your antioxidant levels: matcha green tea and bio-available super-fruits and vegetables help counter the damaging effects of free radicals on cellular health.
  • Supports digestive health: each serve of BODY contains 1 billion probiotics to help re-balance your microbiome.
  • Super-charged nutrients: The Beauty Chef's exclusive Flora Culture fermentation process means you absorb more nutrients from the wholefood ingredients including acerola cherry, mushrooms, grasses, berries, algae, cruciferous vegetables, seeds, spices, fruits and leafy greens.
  • Repairs and rejuvenates: promotes healthy skin and muscle tissue thanks to The Beauty Chef's unique bio-fermented, easily digestible plant-based protein blend.
  • Helps combat oxidative stress and inflammation: one serve contains 100% of your RDI of vitamin C. Vitamin C boosts your levels of glutathione, an antioxidant your body produces naturally to protect itself against free radical damage, inflammation and cellular ageing.
  • Supports bone health and overall wellbeing: each serve supplies 50% of your RDI of vitamin D, helping you absorb more calcium. Studies show that vitamin D has beneficial effects on mood, immunity, glucose metabolism, heart health, hypertension and inflammatory conditions such as arthritis.
  • Helps alkalise your body: The Beauty Chef's bio-fermented and cleansing combination of gut-loving greens supports the detoxification processes.
  • Nutrient-dense fast food: the perfect snack or meal supplement containing an arsenal of amino acids, antioxidants, vitamins, minerals, prebiotics and probiotics to nourish your body, re-balance your belly, boost your metabolic rate and keep you feeling full for longer.
  • Certified Organic: The body inner beauty powder is Certified Organic which means the ingredients are grown and the product is made without any synthetic chemical additives, herbicides or pesticides
Tags: body inner beauty powder, cruelty free, exercise supplement, protein powder, The Beauty Chef, vegan

Does not contain any synthetic amino acids, artificial colourings, flavourings, preservatives, lactose, nuts, sugar, soy or dairy.

Name: Cookbook
Short description: The Beauty Chef founder Carla Oates believes smooth, radiant skin is an inside-out process and that beauty begins in your belly (and your kitchen). this hardcover cook book contains recipes based on her skincare supplements.
Description: The Beauty Chef Cookbook is a comprehensive collection of more than 150 nutritious and delicious recipes to promote gut health and boost beauty from the inside out. The delicious healthy recipes are all gluten and dairy-free as well as super nourishing, and easy to prepare. The book includes simple family meals, healthy spins on traditional dishes, fail-proof ferments, smoothies, lunchbox snacks and special occasion treats that pack a powerful nutritional punch. It's food for radiant skin, good digestion and robust health. The book also includes Carla's practical guide to holistic good health and nutrition. Plus her tips on how to prepare food for optimal nutrition and effective digestion which leads to a happy gut and a glowing complexion. Carla believes unprocessed, organic, low GI (glycaemic index) and low HI (human intervention) foods are the best for our bodies, bellies and skin. Her cookbook contains all the inspiration you need to start feeding your own skin from within. Because beauty really does begin in your belly.
Tags: carla oates, cookbook, the beauty chef perth
Meta: how_to:
Keep this comprehensive cookbook handy in your kitchen and refer to it frequently for all your breakfast, lunch, dinner, snack, savoury and sweet solutions. Use the book to plan your meals for the week ahead, write a shopping list and start cooking your way to a clearer complexion. 

Stock your freezer with some of the delicious desserts for those days when temptation strikes and fill your pantry with jars of lacto-fermented goodness to keep your belly happy. Use the simple fermented drink recipes including kefir, kombucha, kvass, coolers and teas for energy and hydration, to satisfy hunger, ease digestion and wind down. In a nutshell, it’s a beautiful guide to eating well and creating a radiant complexion at the same time.

Name: Probiotic Skin Refiner
Short description: An all-in-one exfoliator, hydrator and collagen booster that is rich in natural probiotics and bio-fermented lactic acid to help smooth, brighten and strengthen all skin types.
Description:
This multi-purpose skin elixir gently exfoliates, balances and hydrates thirsty skin as well as stimulates collagen synthesis for improved tone and texture. It encourages cellular turnover and helps reverse the signs of sun damaged skin and may reduce skin breakouts. The scientifically formulated solution is designed to topically replenish, feed and fortify your skin's ecosystem and microbiome, which is your immune system's first line of defence. The formula contains bio-active wholefood extracts from Certified Organic grains, seeds, grasses, fruits, algae, vegetables and herbs which have been bio-fermented using The Beauty Chef's exclusive, Flora Culture fermentation process to make them more active.   Features and benefits of The Beauty chef probiotic beauty refiner.
  • Soothes inflamed skin: bio-fermented, young coconut extract acts as an anti-inflammatory, anti-bacterial, anti-fungal ingredient and encourages the healing process.
  • Smooths appearance: bio-activated coconut oil is rich in fatty acids that help encourage skin-cell repair and rejuvenation, and smooth fine lines and wrinkles.
  • Protects skin surface: helps repair and restore your skin's natural lipid barrier by replacing lipids lost due to UV exposure, stress and other environmental damage.
  • Rejuvenates the skin: bio-fermented nutrients in the balm are better absorbed by your skin and therefore help to rejuvenate the skin's deeper layers.
  • Hydrates skin: the unique blend of phospholipids, essential fatty acids, vitamins and minerals give the balm excellent conditioning and emollient properties, helping to hydrate your skin and prevent moisture loss.
  • suitable for all skin types.

Name: Serum Foundation
Short description: Lightweight pigment suspension system with moderate coverage.
Description: The Ordinary serum foundation is a lightweight medium-coverage formulation available in 21 comprehensive shades. The foundation has a semi-matte finish that looks natural with a very lightweight dewy feel. The shades are divided into three categories: 1 for fair to lighter tones, 2 for medium tones; and 3 for darker tones. Each category is then classified further by a second digit from 0 to 3 to indicate depth within each category. Finally, a letter is added to the shade code to identify the undertone: P (Pink) and R (Red) indicate cool undertones for lighter and darker shades respectively; N indicates a Neutral tone; Y indicates a Yellow undertone. View The Ordinary shade guide > The pigments used in this format are treated for a rich, highly-saturated effect. These pigments are suspended in our proprietary spreadability system that allows pigments to look natural on the skin, resist collecting within fine lines and stay on for longer. The foundations are compatible with most primers and are designed to work exceptionally well with the primers offering from The Ordinary. As with most liquid forms of foundation, it's ideal to shake the container lightly before use.

Name: No. 1 Green Goddess Detox Jar
Short description: This herbal tisane tastes divine and has the added benefit of powerful cleansing actions. St Mary's thistle, schizandra and dandelion root work to detoxify your liver, while citrus peel and lemongrass promote lightness and radiance.
Description: St Mary's Thistle: St Mary's thistle is unique in its ability to protect the liver. The compounds in St Mary's thistle work together to support healthy liver function and tissue integrity by supporting healthy cellular defenses. St Mary's thistle also aids in the elimination of toxin accumulation in the liver and in the support of hormonal processes?in the body. Schizandra: Schizandra is known as one of the most powerful  youth tonics  of all time and is prized by Asian cultures for its ability to enhance youthfulness, increase stamina and prevent fatigue. Schizandra fruits or berries contain various lignans, compounds that enhance the immune system, protect the liver and improve the body's ability to handle stress. Dandelion Root: Dandelion has been shown to improve liver function by removing toxins, re-hydrating, and re-establishing the body's electrolyte balance. The herb also acts as a diuretic, assisting the kidneys in clearing out waste, salt, and excess water. The dandelion plant is rich in antioxidants that may prevent free-radical damage to cells and DNA.
Tags: edible beat green goddess, edible beauty perth, edible beauty tea

Hibiscus contains flavonoids and anthocyanins, which have antioxidant properties and have been shown to support heart health. Papaya:Called the fruit of the angels by Christopher Columbus, papaya is a great source of antioxidant nutrients such as carotene, vitamin C and flavonoids. Papaya also contains the digestive enzyme papain, which assists digestion and may assist in reducing inflammation in the body.

Short description: A skin cleaning system that respects dermal barriers while regulating visible sebum production, cleaning the skin thoroughly and removing all traces of makeup in a single step.
Description:
?Low-Viscosity Cleaning Ester?contains no cleansing plant oils, no detergents and no water but instead uses isolated sugar and avocado esters to remove every trace of dirt and makeup with or without water. While the skin feels comfortably hydrated after each use, the technologies in Low-Viscosity Cleaning Ester will actually further act as delivery boosters for topical treatments applied after cleaning.   • Fatty alcohol ethylhexanoic acid ester: Not to be mistaken for alcohol or acids, this incredibly emollient and skin-friendly ester takes the approach of using the enemy's strength to win against the enemy?its structure is nearly identical to a vast array of emollients used in makeup and skincare (the enemy of clean skin), allowing this ester to reconstitute?or breakdown?these formulations solely by being so similar to them.   • Catalyzed avocado butyl alcohol ester: A true evolution in green biochemistry, this patented avocado ester is able to clean the skin instantly of nearly every hydrophobic substance while clinically shown to balance sebum activity so that both dry skin and oily skin can benefit equally toward normalized behaviour.
  • Gallic acid ester: Both a cleaning ester and a potent antioxidant, this technology facilitates the removal of?Low-Viscosity Cleaning Ester itself once other technologies are bound to surface impurities. As this ester is the last-man standing and closest-reacting to the skin, its antioxidant function is of significant value, offering tissue-adhering, water-free oxidative protection on a daily basis.

Short description: A three-phase rinse-off cleansing and decongestion system that does not disrupt the skin surface equilibrium or density.
Description: This formulation can be likened to a masque, but it does much more than temporarily clear the skin. 1. Purifying Phase This phase is the simplest one in the formulation and the one that is most closely aligned with masques as they are known today. In this phase, surface impurities, which includes oil, and water-soluble pollution, cosmetic product build-up and excess sebum activity build-up are physically solubilized and removed. This step is assisted by the presence of black Amazonian clay with very high concentrations of titanium, and white clay that binds excess sebum. 2. Protective Phase This phase of the formulation offers the most innovative approach to decongestion by introducing technologies that offer a physical shield against external build-up. The inclusion of sea polysaccharide from microorganisms found in Polynesian coral reefs fights build up of urban pollution, acting as a shield against external aggression and allows for better response to climate changes which occur even when not travelling. Advanced analogue of resveratrol enables a first-ever topical utility of this incredible molecule, fights against the look of "browning". A bio-technological derivative of bitter orange peel reduces the look of inflammation as a result of environmental factors. An ultra-pure bisabolol?with up to 900 times less impurity than standard German chamomile flower derivatives?reduces the look inflammation through a secondary support mechanism while forming mild but sustainable support against climate change. 3. Responsive Phase This phase of the formulation introduces mechanisms that fight against environmental congestion factors. This phase is the most important phase as it respects health and longevity. A highly-purified flavanone derived from the inner white parts of citrus peel, triggers topical visible detoxification. A pre-cursor to a modified oleic acid that is naturally produced on normal skin by a yeast offers a slow, non-abrupt, increase of this acid without disrupting dermal pH or density. Meta: how_to: Mr Smith Blond is a treatment mask designed to be used after shampooing and before conditioning. Apply to hair and leave in for 30 seconds to 3 minutes, depending on hair porosity and level of toning needed, before rinsing out. On first use we recommend leaving Mr Smith Blond in for only 30 seconds, in order to avoid over-toning hair. Hair with stronger yellow tones may need more time, and very porous hair will need less. If hair is excessively pigmented after use, re-wash with your usual Mr Smith shampoo, rinse, and condition if required.

Short description: COSRX Advanced snail 96 mucin power essence is the filtrated snail secretion, extracted from snails and used as an essence to hydrate and protect the skin barrier.\n\nRest assured no snails are harmed during this process.
Description:
Formulated with 96 per cent filtered snail secretion, this  COSRX essence protects the skin from moisture loss, fades acne scars and hyperpigmentation, treats fine lines, and soothes the skin (great for sunburn). What is Snail Mucin? This Korean skincare ingredient is literally the filtrated secretion of mucous from snails.  Snail  mucin is naturally secreted from snails and is used by snails as a way to protect themselves. this is turn can help protect your skin barrier. The mucin extraction process is a cruelty free process and no snails are harmed during this process.  Use this essence after cleansing and toning and before applying serums and treatments.   Free from parabens sulphate and alcohol. This  COSRX toner contains 4 %  natural BHA  , which is a chemical exfoliator that penetrates deeper into the layer of the skin to gently remove dirt and sebum from inside pores. Meta: presenter:
About Barbara Cavalli

Barbara Cavalli comes to skin care from a successful career as a commercial and fashion make-up artist. For years she was exposed to people who were in desperate need of help with their skin. Over time they had given up on their complexion and were relying on expensive make-up as a solution to cover their skin issues. They were hungry to know what she knew about skin health and care because everything they read or heard was so confusing, not to mention expensive. Since then Barbara has been on a mission to learn, develop and then teach how to care for your skin in a simple, effective and affordable way. To cut through the myths and marketing nonsense in a quest to give her clients back their confidence and their healthy skin! She is exceedingly proud to partner with Vim&Co in this series of workshops and help people in their journey to healthy, beautiful skin. Barbara was recently featured on Urban List as one of Perth’s top facial therapists.
Meta: long_desc_tab:
Taking care of your skin doesn’t have to be hard, just as long as it’s done right. In this 90 minute workshop, leading Perth facial therapist takes a comprehensive and holistic approach to skincare where she will cover:
  • Identifying your skin type
  • Identifying common skin conditions
  • How your lifestyle, work environment and diet is impacting your skin & changes you should make
  • Common skincare mistakes
  • The difference between plant-based skincare and pharmaceutical products
  • How to choose the right products for your skin
  • Knowing what skincare products are essential
  • Your questions.
Barbara will also help you choose the right products for you in store and share her favourite products.

Meta: presenter:
About Julie Meek

With over 20 years’ experience in diet and nutrition, Julie Meek is Perth’s top Sports Dietician. You can listen to Julie on Talk Back Radio. Her extensive career has seen her work with Olympic athletes and elite sports stars at Perth Glory Soccer Club, Perth Wildcats, Fremantle Dockers, and the Western Australian Institute of Sport. Julie is passionate about taking a holistic approach to health and covers all things food, health, nutrition, and performance on her blog and radio 6PR 882AM.
Meta: long_desc_tab:
Intermittent fasting is becoming one of the hottest trends in the world of health, well-being and nutrition. Many people are jumping on board with the hope of reducing weight, improving their risk of lifestyle diseases and to slow that ageing process down.

Claims abound on the proclaimed powerful effects of intermittent fasting but are they real? Join Julie Meek for an evening of discovery into intermittent fasting, the benefits and practicalities, and whether this style of eating is designed for you.

Meta: _yoast_wpseo_title: Vim & Co Workshops | Skin Prep and Beauty Basics
Meta: presenter: Erin Maie Latkovic, Makeup Artist  As one of Perth’s most highly regarded and talented makeup artists, Erin has a passion for enhancing her clients’ natural features without masking the skin and all of its beauty. Her work is a celebration of the skin and her signature look often features natural and glowing finishes complemented by natural hues and brushed up brows. With over 9 years’ experience working as a freelance makeup artist, Erin has worked on a myriad of commercial and creative projects spanning celebrities, weddings, runway, advertising, music videos and events. Be sure to follow Erin on instagram here.   Yen Tran, Founder and Pharmacist, Vim & Co With over 18 years experience as a Pharmacist, Yen brings a love for skincare and quality skincare products and passion for the science and technology behind skincare innovations to help address Vim & Co’s customers skincare concerns and needs. Yen adopts a consultative approach to skincare in store, helping customers navigate various skincare products, formulations and ingredients to address their specific concerns and requirements.
Meta: long_desc_tab:
This interactive, two part, 60-minute session is the perfect introduction to skincare and beauty and a brilliant opportunity to learn practical skincare and makeup application tips to enhance your natural beauty. Whether you are a complete beauty novice or someone looking for an easy, every day look, this workshop is a casual, fun and interactive platform to trial some new products, ask questions and learn some easy to apply skincare and beauty techniques. PART ONE: The session will commence with an introduction to skincare and skin preparation with Vim & Co’s Founder and Pharmacist, Yen Tran. Yen will provide an overview on:
  • The importance of skin health as a foundation for makeup
  • Makeup removal, the importance of removing makeup and the best products to consider
  • A simple, effective skincare regime including cleansers, toners and moisturisers suitable for different skin types
  • The role of treatment products including masks, mud masks, acids (the difference between AHA and BHA acid exfoliators), Vitamin C, Oils and Retinol, targeted toward specific skin concerns.
PART TWO: Perth Makeup Artist, Erin Maie, will then join us to introduce you to some of our favourite multi-purpose beauty products and how to incorporate simple techniques for a natural finish including;
  • The do’s and don'ts of choosing beauty products touching on:
    • Ingredients/textures to avoid for different skin
    • Choosing colours to suit your complexion
    • Mixing cream and powder products
  • Tips and tricks for using multi-purpose beauty products
  • Applying Foundation including:
    • Colour matching
    • Application tools - beauty blender, brush or fingers
    • Using setting sprays and powders
    • Achieving a flawless finish without going full coverage
Erin and Yen will also make time at the conclusion of the formal session to help you shop in-store for personal products and answer any specific skincare and beauty questions. Due to the interactive nature of this workshop, places are limited. Call (08) 9328 9447 to book your seat!
Meta: _yoast_wpseo_metadesc: An interactive two-part beauty basics workshop guiding you through some simple skincare and beauty techniques for a no-fuss, everyday, natural look.

Name: Inner Health for Kids Powder
Short description: A daily probiotic powder for kids to promote gut health and restoration.\nThis probiotic requires refrigeration and is only available for in store pick up.
Description:
Ethical Nutrients Inner Health Kids Powder may:
  • Promote the growth and increase the number of healthy bacteria within the digestive system
  • Support a normal healthy gastrointestinal system
  • Help improve general wellbeing
  • Assist in maintaining the balance of good bacteria when a child has been taking a course of antibiotics
Size: 60g NOTE: As this product is refrigerated, it cannot be shipped and is available for collection at the pharmacy only. If you would like to pay for the product over the phone in advance of collection, please call us on (08) 9328 9447.
Tags: gut health, kids, kids health, Probiotic, Supplement
Meta: ingredients:
Each 2.3g dose contains 13.5 Billion Live Bacteria:
Lactobacillus rhamnosus (LGG®) 6 Billion
Lactobacillus acidophilus (NCFM®) 3.75 Billion
Bifidobacterium lactis (Bi-07) 3.75 Billion
Meta: how_to:
Children from 0 to 12 years:
Take 2.3 g (1 metric teaspoon) daily mixed into water, juice, formula or milk (warm or cold). Sprinkle on cereal, food or take directly o the spoon.

Antibiotic use: If your child has been taking a course of antibiotics, take 2.3 g (1 dry level metric teaspoon) twice daily.

Alternatively, take as advised by a healthcare professional. Inner Health Kids is non-flavoured with a naturally sweet taste.

The powder should be refrigerated at 2-8 degrees Celcius. Do not freeze.

Supplements should not replace a balanced diet.  If symptoms persist, consult your healthcare professional. Do not use if cap and/or bottle seals are missing or broken.

Name: Clear Skin
Short description: A daily supplement for the maintenance of healthy skin combining herbs traditionally used for the management of minor skin disorders with nutrients vitamins A, B6 and zinc.
Description:
Herbs of Gold Clear Skin is formulated with a range of herbs and nutrients which may provide relief from acne, assist in repairing and healing skin and maintaining healthy skin. This formulation may be of benefit due to the traditional uses of:
  • Burdock -? traditionally used for the symptomatic relief of mild eczema, mild psoriasis, boils, mild acne, mild skin eruptions and for the management of minor skin disorders due to its blood cleansing and purifying action.
  • Yellow dock -? traditionally used for the management of minor skin disorders due to its purifying action and for the symptomatic relief of mild eczema, mild psoriasis, mild acne and minor skin conditions.
  • Yellow dock - traditionally used for minor skin disorders associated with constipation or sluggish bowel.
  • Echinacea - traditionally used for the symptomatic relief of mild eczema and mild psoriasis and, with Calendula, assists minor wound healing. Echinacea is traditionally used for the management of minor skin disorders due to its blood cleansing and purifying action.
  • Vitamin A and zinc - act as antioxidants, protecting cells from free radical damage and oxidative stress and are important for the maintenance of a healthy immune system.
  • Vitamins A and B6 - help maintain the health and integrity of the skin. Vitamin B6 is required for the healthy formation of collagen.
  • Zinc - required for normal skin repair and helps maintain healthy skin. Zinc may assist in minor wound healing and the relief of minor skin disorders such as mild acne.

  • Provides 200mg of Meriva® curcumin daily, with absorption equal to 5400mg of regular curcumin (or 16.5g of fresh Turmeric)

  • May support joint health and act as an antioxidant, reducing free radicals formed in the body
  • Is a soy free formula

Short description: A high-quality dissolvable collagen supplement for the maintenance of healthy skin, hair and nails.
Description:
Herbs of Gold Collagen Gold is a high-quality source of collagen combined with a unique superfood blend that helps the body maintain normal healthy skin, hair and nails. Collagen is the body?s most abundant protein, representing approximately 30% of total body protein. Collagen is a major structural component of connective tissue found in the body - in skin, hair, nails, ligaments, tendons, cartilage, teeth and bone. Collagen provides tensile strength and firmness to connective tissues around the body. Herbs of Gold Collagen Gold may help to promote collagen production and replenish lost or declining levels of collagen, slowing down visible signs of aging including fine lines, wrinkles, and sagging skin and help to stabilise and strengthen joints by preventing collagen breakdown. This supplement contains:
  • Fish collagen which is rich in essential and non-essential amino acids and contains a minimum of 90% protein from fish collagen and 8% hydroxyproline (responsible for collagen stability) in each serve. Collagen Gold contains type I collagen, the most abundant collagen type found in the body, predominantly found in the skin, tendons, ligaments and bone.
  • A specially selected superfood blend containing Yangmei (Yumberry), Pomegranate, Acai and Acerola berries providing a rich source of natural vitamin C for antioxidant protection and is essential in a number of steps for collagen production and helping to prevent the breakdown of collagen. Guava provides natural zinc, important for protein synthesis and skin structure.
Contains 180g of powder NOTE: Prior to shipping of all vitamins and supplements, Vim & Co's Pharmacists will review your order and may be in contact (if they deem necessary) to discuss your medical history and existing medications, in relation to any products where contraindications may exist.

  • Vitamin C provides natural antihistamine activity so plays an important role in balancing and maintaining healthy histamine levels.?

Name: Memory and Cognition Gold
Short description: A daily supplement with brahmi, additional herbs and nutrients to support healthy memory, cognitive function, concentration and focus.
Description:
Herbs of Gold Memory & Cognition Gold helps maintain and enhance cognitive function, memory, focus and concentration. It uses BacoMind,  an extract of Bacopa monnieri (clinically trialled brahmi*), that contains a unique combination of active constituents. Brahmi is traditionally used in Ayurvedic medicine to enhance cognitive function and memory. BacoMind supports cognitive function and memory during aging and also supports learning and memory, including information retention and recall, in children and adolescents. This supplement also contains:
  • Ginkgo to help maintain blood flow to the brain, thereby assisting in the maintenance of cognitive function, memory, focus and concentration.
  • Panax ginseng, an invigorating herb beneficial during periods of fatigue and poor concentration and helps to restore mental concentration capacity.
  • L-theanine, an amino acid found almost exclusively in tea. L-theanine helps maintain healthy brain function by regulation of neurotransmitters.
  • Phosphatidylserine, the major phospholipid in the brain and is important for cellular communication, which helps improve the transfer of signals between brain cells.
*Morgan A. et al. Name: Cold and Flu
Short description:
Vim & Co has a range of over the counter products available to treat common cold and flu symptoms.
Products in this range include day and night cold and flu tablets, nasal sprays, throat lozenges, throat gargles and sprays and immune boosters.
Cold and flu tablets contain either pseudoephedrine or phenylephrine as a primary decongestant to unblock stuffy noses or sinuses and clear the foggy, heavy-headed feeling that comes with a cold.
They will usually also have paracetamol to help with pain or fever. The night time component usually contains an antihistamine ingredient that helps to dry up a runny nose and to cause drowsiness, to aid in sleep.
Some cold and flu tablets may or may not contain an ingredient for cough and it's usually an ingredient for a dry cough rather than a wet/chesty cough.
Along with many variations of cold and flu tablets- for day, night or both, with and without an ingredient for cough - comes a whole range of other products that help with the symptoms of a cold, like sore throat and fever. There are also natural health options that may help to boost the body's natural immune system and these can be used in conjunction with traditional medicines that are available over the counter.
Why should I talk to the pharmacist?
Oral decongestants are not suitable for patients with high uncontrolled blood pressure and those on other medications. Our Pharmacist can recommend safe alternative options based on your current medical conditions and other medications you are taking.
Need a consult? We welcome the opportunity to provide one-on-one consults to discuss your health concerns. Consults allow us to undertake necessary screening to determine whether referral to other medical professionals is required, ensure the right products are recommended for you (with information on the correct and effective use of those products) and provide additional lifestyle and primary care advice to optimise your recovery and general health. Consults with one of our Pharmacists are available in person or over the phone. Please call us today on (08) 9328 9447 or visit us in-store.
Tags: cold and flu, Over the counter medicines, pharmacy advice, services

Name: Allerge (30 Capsules)
Short description: A Herbal formula used in traditional Chinese medicine to ease mild allergy symptoms like hayfever and mild food intolerances.
Description:
Oriental Botanicals AllergE contains a blend of herbs known as Minor Bupleurum Combination, which has been used for around 3000 years in TCM, where it's traditionally used to improve the body's resistance to allergens. According to TCM philosophy, it works by tonifying Lung Qi, the form of life force energy (or Qi) that's associated with the Lung organ-meridian system. In Chinese medicine, key herbs in Minor Bupleurum Combination are traditionally used to relieve a variety of mild allergy symptoms, and some have additional benefits for digestive, skin or respiratory-related symptoms, as detailed below. Key ingredients & Benefits of Oriental Botanicals Allerge formula:
  • Contains a blend of herbs called Minor Bupleurum Combination, which is traditionally used to improve the body's resistance to allergens in TCM, where it's believed to work by tonifying Lung Qi
  • Baical skullcap, traditionally used to relieve mild allergy symptoms in TCM, and to help manage hayfever and mild eczema and hives
  • Bupleurum, traditionally used to ease mild food intolerance symptoms such as digestive discomfort, nausea, bloating and diarrhoea in TCM
  • Korean ginseng to calm inflamed, hot and itchy skin conditions like mild eczema and hives, based on its traditional use in TCM
  •  Chinese licorice, traditionally taken to relieve mild bronchial irritation and respiratory mucus (catarrh) in TCM
Capsules: 30 NOTE: Prior to shipping of all vitamins and supplements, Vim & Co's Pharmacists will review your order and may be in contact (if they deem necessary) to discuss your medical history and existing medications, in relation to any products where contraindications may exist.
Tags: allergies, dietary supplement, hayfever, oriental botanicals, tcm

Short description: A herbal formula  used to support immune health plus reduce cold & flu frequency in traditional Chinese & Western herbal medicine.
Description:
Chinese herbal medicine Oriental Botanicals  Astragalus 8 is used to help the immune system and support a return to good health. The herbs in Astragalus 8 have been used for centuries to help people strengthen their body's defences and restore good health. Astragalus 8 is based on an ancient Chinese therapy called Fu Zheng Pei Ben. In Chinese medicine terms Fu Zheng means to rectify and support the normal, healthy vital energy (Qi) of all body systems, while Pei Ben means to strengthen the resistance mechanisms of the body especially those relating to healthy immune function. The scientifically proven herb Astragalus is combined with seven other potent immune system herbs including Ganoderma (Reishi), Codonopsis, Atractylodes, Shisandra, Siberian ginseng, Ligustrum and Licorice to create this modern Chinese herbal medicine. Benefits of Astragalus 8 formula may include:
  • Promoting a healthy immune system
  • Enhancing recovery during convalescence
  • Reducing the risk of developing colds and flu
  • Enhancing recovery post-operatively and following illness
  • Helping to restore good health

Name: Kidnetone (30 Tablets)
Short description: Herbs traditionally used as kidney tonics and to regulate body fluids in Chinese medicine.
Description:
Oriental Botanicals Kidnetone combines the kidney tonic herbs goji berry, rehmannia and horny goat weed to regulate body fluids. Supporting a healthy kidney organ-meridian system by using kidney tonic herbs is traditionally seen as beneficial for other body functions too, including maintaining healthy hearing and promoting bone strength. Oriental Botanicals Kidnetone is based on a traditional Chinese herbal formula for the kidney organ-meridian system called Six-Ingredient Rehmannia Pill, which has been used for around 900 years. Benefits of Kidnetone formula:
  • Rehmannia, traditionally used in Chinese medicine to support kidney health in multiple ways, including by helping to boost and invigorate Jing, a form of life force energy that's stored in the kidneys. Jing is inherited from your parents in fixed quantities at the time of your conception, and your levels of it progressively decline as you get older, so maintaining healthy levels of Jing becomes increasingly important from mid-life onwards. Rehmannia is also used as a liver tonic, and as a blood tonic that helps relieve sleeplessness and irregular menstrual cycles. It's traditionally regarded as having nourishing effects on the kidneys' Yin qualities, and when Kidney and Liver Yin are deficient, is used to relieve excessive night-time perspiration and to support healthy hearing.
  • Goji berries, traditionally used as a kidney tonic to regulate body fluids and relieve fatigue and feelings of weakness in traditional Chinese medicine, and like rehmannia, is traditionally used to strengthen and enrich Jing. These antioxidant-rich berries are also traditionally regarded as a longevity tonic from this methodology. Goji berries are traditionally used to nourish and replenish both Yin and Yang, keeping them in balance in the body. If levels of Yin become deficient (or too low relative to Yang), goji berries are also traditionally used to relieve the resulting symptoms, which can include excessive sweating at night and mild dizziness.
  • Horny goat weed, traditionally regarded as having Yang-strengthening effects in traditional Chinese medicine. As well as supporting healthy kidney function and helping to regulate body fluids, it's traditionally used as a kidney tonic that enhances healthy libido, as well as to strengthen the bones and relieve mild aches and pains of the joints.
  • Cornelian Cherry, Chinese yam, Alisma and Poria.
Tablets: 30 NOTE: Prior to shipping of all vitamins and supplements, Vim & Co's Pharmacists will review your order and may be in contact (if they deem necessary) to discuss your medical history and existing medications, in relation to any products where contraindications may exist.

Short description: An active CoQ10 150mg with superior absorption and bioavailability to combat oxidative stress.
Description:
Ubiquinol BioActive is the reduced (active) form of coenzyme Q10. As the active form of coenzyme Q10, ubiquinol has superior absorption and higher bioavailability than other forms of coenzyme Q10 such as ubiquinone/ubidecarenone. Ubiquinol supports healthy energy synthesis, and is a highly efficient antioxidant to combat oxidative stress associated with increasing age, including oxidation of LDL cholesterol. It may be of benefit to people experiencing increased oxidative stress as occurs with normal healthy ageing. The active Ubiquinol form provides:
  • enhanced absorption
  • highly efficient antioxidant activity
  • maintenance of healthy LDL cholesterol levels in healthy people.

Name: InNatal
Short description: Comprehensive formula with activated B vitamins combining key nutrients for pregnancy, breastfeeding and in the preconception phase.
Description:
Bioceuticals InNatal is a specially formulated multivitamin providing a broad range of well-researched nutrients to assist women in meeting many of the increased nutritional requirements during preconception, pregnancy and breastfeeding. The formula contains activated B vitamins to assist with energy production during times of stress. It also provides nutrients important for supporting the healthy growth and development of the foetus and baby including iodine, folinic acid, MTHF, vitamin D3, choline and zinc. The use of multinutrients during preconception and pregnancy has been positively linked with healthy pregnancy outcomes. Benefits of Bioceuticals InNatal formula:
  • This formulation provide several key nutrients for pregnancy including iodine, vitamin D3, choline, zinc, folinic acid and MTHF.
  • Provides 500mcg of vitamin B9 as the activated forms of folic acid. Folic acid, if taken daily by women for one month before conception and during pregnancy, may help reduce the risk of having a child with the neural tube defects known as spina bifida and anencephaly.
  • Contains some B vitamins in their activated forms.
  • Provides 1000IU of vitamin D3 per daily dose and vitamin K2 in the form of menaquinone 7 (MK-7). Vitamins K2 and D3 and involved in the maintenance and development of strong healthy bones.
  • Divided daily dose allows for smaller capsules for increased compliance.
  • suitable for vegans
Soft Capsule: 60 NOTE: Bioceuticals is a practitioner-only brand and a one-on-one consultation with one of our Pharmacists is required prior to purchase. For product pricing and consultations, please call us on (08) 9328 9447 or visit us in-store.

Name: Acetyl L-Carnitine
Short description: Acetyl L-Carnitine helps your body turn fatty acids into energy, with an amino acid that plays a role in cellular energy production and also supports healthy brain function.
Description:
Acetyl-L-carnitine (ALC, acetyllevocarnitine) is the naturally occurring acetyl ester of L-carnitine and is the delivery form for both L-carnitine and acetyl groups. Carnitine is an amino acid required for normal healthy lipid and carbohydrate metabolism. It is concentrated in cardiac and skeletal cells where it helps deliver fatty acids into mitochondria for cellular energy production. High concentrations are also found in the male reproductive tract and the brain. When acetylated in the form of ALC, it readily crosses the blood-brain barrier to support neuronal energetics and repair mechanisms while modifying acetylcholine production in the central nervous system (CNS). Benefits of Bioceuticals acetyl-l-carnitine:
  • Assists the transport of long-chain fatty acids (LCFA) into mitochondria, where they are oxidised for the synthesis of cellular energy.
  • Supports normal healthy lipid and carbohydrate metabolism.
  • Provides nutritional support and antioxidant protection for healthy cell membrane integrity.
  • Balances and supports normal male physiology and function.
  • Plays a role in normal healthy sperm motility.
  • Supports healthy brain function.
  • Supports healthy ageing.
Capsules: 90 NOTE: Bioceuticals is a practitioner-only brand and a one-on-one consultation with one of our Pharmacists is required prior to purchase. For product pricing and consultations, please call us on (08) 9328 9447 or visit us in-store. Vitamin and mineral supplements should not replace a balanced diet. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use.

  • Contains some B vitamins in their activated forms.
  • Provides 1000IU of vitamin D3 per daily dose and vitamin K2 in the form of menaquinone 7 (MK-7). Vitamins K2 and D3 and involved in the maintenance and development of strong healthy bones.

Name: EB Tea Jar - No. 7 &ROSE PU-ERH
Description:
CLEANSING | DETOXIFYING | BOOSTING

This tisane is made with Pu-erh tea, a fermented black tea with strong cleansing properties and an unmistakably earthy and delicious natural flavour. In Traditional Chinese Medicine Pu-erh is renowned for its ability to cleanse and purify, assist in enhancing the metabolism and facilitating weight loss.

Botanical Actives
  • Pu-erh Tea For more than 1,700 years, the Chinese have been drinking Pu-erh tea especially as a digsetif after a heavy meal. The tea has a deliciously mellow and deeply earthy flavour and is traditionally aged underground. In recent years, studies investigating the health benefits of Pu-erh tea have shown that it has antioxidant effects and may assist in reducing weight loss.
  • White Tea White tea, grown and harvested in the Chinese province of Fujian, is the least processed of all teas. White tea contains the same types of antioxidants as green tea, but in greater quantities. These potent antioxidants have been found to have many potential health benefits, including boosting cardiovascular health and enhancing weight loss. Studies have found that white tea?s anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties may also slow the breakdown of the skin?s elastin and collagen, enhancing the youthful appearance of skin.
Tags: fermented black tea, metabolism, No. 7, ROSE PU-ERH, weight loss
Meta: ingredients: Pu-erh, Rose Petals*, White Tea*. *Denotes organic ingredient
Meta: how_to: Add 1 tspn per cup of boiling water. Infuse for 5 to 8 minutes. Store in a cool and dry place. A dash of milk may be added after the tea has brewed.

COMPOSITION AND CARE

Make sure the wick is alight properly to create an even wax pool for the first time burning it. Cut the top of the wick approx 5mm before each use to ensure an even burn.

Keep away from draughts or flammable objects

Meta: how_to:
HOT
Lay flat in microwave and heat for 1-2 minutes on high (850 watt microwave). Turnover halfway through the heating time to prevent heat spots. If further heating is required, repeat in increments of 20-39 seconds until desired temperature is reached.

DO NOT OVERHEAT. SPOT CLEAN ONLY.

Warnings: Discard if there is a burnt odour. Do not use on sensitive skin, infants or anyone who is sleeping. Do not use when wet. Leave to cool on a fire-resistant surface after use and do not put into storage until cool. Replace pillow after prolonged use or if it appears damaged.

COLD
Place in freezer bag and freeze for 1-2 hours before use.

Name: Coverage Foundation
Short description: A high coverage foundation available across 21 shades. Containing more pigment that The Ordinary's serum foundation this range offers more coverage with a non oily cream finish.
Description:
The Ordinary Coverage Foundation A full-coverage foundation that is available in a comprehensive shade range across 21 shades. These foundations contain higher pigment levels than our serum foundations but still offer a smooth finish that avoids the heavy makeup look that can make skin appear more aged. The texture is lightweight and gives you a matte & dewy finish which is suitable for oily skin! The shades are divided into four categories (Each category is then classified further by a second digit from 0 to 3 to indicate depth within each category):
  • 1 for fair to lighter tones
  • 2 for medium tones
  • 3 for darker tones.
Finally, a letter is added to the shade code to identify the undertone: P (Pink) and R (Red) indicate cool undertones for lighter and darker shades respectively; N (Neutral tone); Y (Yellow undertone). For a complete shade guide, please click here!

Meta: how_to:
As with most liquid forms of foundation, it's ideal to shake the container lightly before use.

Pump a small amount into the palm or the back of your hand.

Smooth on and blend throughout the face with a brush, a damp beauty blender (particularly if you have large pores, rosacea, or textured bumps), or simply your fingertips ideally outward from the midpoint of the face.

If irritation occurs, rinse off, cease use, and consult a physician.

Use only as directed on unbroken skin.

Patch testing prior to use is advised.

Keep out of reach of children.

Description:
Our Natural Plant Based Repair Balm made from key New Zealand ingredients such as M?nuka Honey, Kawakawa and Mamuka. It aids in the soothing and repair of insect bites, stings, skin rashes, poor circulation, bruises, wounds, burns, aches, pains, sunburn, dry cracked skin, eczema, psoriasis and inflammation. This will become a regular in your medicine cabinet especially if you have young children. We have included key New Zealand ingredients for their unique healing properties.

Kawakawa leaves were traditionally used topically for numerous conditions including, bruises, rheumatism, dry - irritated skin and minor cuts and infections. Kawakawa leaves contain volatile oil and two key components of this, Myristicin and Elemicin have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory properties.

Aloe Vera Oil is a good emollient and excellent moisturizing agent.

Hemp oil is considered to have anti-inflammatory properties, with its essential fatty acids useful in assisting skin conditions.

M?nuka Honey harbours a number of health properties: antibacterial, antioxidant, anti-inflammatory and antifungal. This makes honey effective as both a medicine and a functional food. Research has shown honey can help boost immunity and treat skin infections.

Short description: This is an antioxidant fruit oil contains omega 7 and  other fatty acids that protect the skin against free radical damage to protect its barrier function. Mix with other treatments in the palm of your hand. May stain skin and clothing due to intense colour of oil.
Description:
This The Ordinary  formulation contains 100% pure Sea-Buckthorn Fruit oil that is sustainably-sourced, organic, unrefined and virgin in origin. This exceptional Sea-Buckthorn Fruit oil is derived from the pulp of the Sea-Buckthorn berry.

This oil contains a high concentration of rare Omega 7 for nourishing & protecting the skin.

It also offers other fatty acids like palmitic acid, stearic acid, oleic acid, linolenic acid and linoleic acid as well as antioxidants like tocopherol (Vitamin E), carotenoids and lycopene that all help to protect the skin from free radical damage and to maintain the skin's normal barrier function.

Notes: Supplied in UV-protective packaging. This Sea-Buckthorn Fruit oil is completely unrefined and imparts a natural scent due to its high palmitoleic acid (Omega-7) content. This scent is not an indication of rancidity. Sea-Buckthorn Fruit oil that does not have scent is likely to have been highly refined and, therefore, would contain less active compounds and would likely offer impaired benefits. The formula's intense natural orange-red hue is due to its high carotenoids and lycopene content. After application, the colour of this oil will remain on your skin until it is washed off. Please use a very small amount or dilute with other products for easier application.

Meta: how_to: Use once or twice a week on thoroughly clean, dry skin. Do not use on wet skin. Apply evenly across face using fingertips, avoiding the eye area. Leave on for no more than 10 minutes. Rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water. Do not use on sensitive, peeling or compromised skin. Avoid the eye contour and contact with eyes both during application and rinse off. Patch testing prior to use is advised: Apply the product as directed to a small area once a day for three days to test if you are sensitive to this product. If you develop severe irritation, hives, swelling of eyes and mouth, blistering, or difficulty breathing, rinse off, cease use and consult a physician right away. Keep out of reach of children.

Name: Survival 0 - 30ml
Short description: NIOD Survival 0 is a night serum that is a multi-targeted defense system against environmental aggressors.
Description:
NIOD Survival 0 is a night serum that is a multi-targeted defense system against environmental aggressors. Defend your skin against multiple free radicals found in the air, as well as glycation and advanced glycation end products (shortened to AGE, and known for their role in premature ageing), pollution and smog, stress, infrared and blue light.   NIOD Survival 0 may be used during the day underneath a UV protective product, however it is unnecessary to use it in conjunction with any of the other Survival serums during the day time. You may use one of the Survival 10/20/30 serums during the day, and NIOD Survival 0 during the night for extremely comprehensive defense against multiple skin aggressors.  

Who is NIOD Survival 0 for?

  • All skin types
  • All skin tones
  • Ideal to defend against premature ageing

What?s the difference between NIOD Survival 0 and Survival 10, 20 and 30?

While the NIOD Survival series in 10, 20 and 30 offer SPF10 PA++, SPF20 PA++ and SPF30 PA++ respectively, NIOD Survival 0 is designed to be used in the evening, so does not contain SPF. Survival 0 is effectively the daytime or nighttime version of NIOD Survival 10/20/30, offering the same level of antioxidant support to prepare your skin for the next day, or to defend your skin during the day. For daytime use, however, it must be used under SPF protection.  

What makes NIOD Survival 0 special?

NIOD Survival 0 uses a broad range of technologies to counteract many different types of environmental, age-related, or lifestyle related aggressors.
  • Pycnogenol? is a potent antioxidant that helps to reverse photodamage
  • Tomato Carotenoid Complex helps prevent sunburn from a broad range of the invisible light spectrum
  • Dimethylmethoxy Chromanol helps to neutralise reactive oxygen and nitrogen particles, being proven to be more effective than reseveratrol and ferulic acid
  • Purified Lutein improves elasticity in the skin and helps counteract the effect of blue light
  • Yeast-Derived Superoxide Dismutase helps the skin fight the damaging effect of oxidation in skin cells
  • Fractionated Melanin is tailored to absorb light within a specific range of wavelengths to defend from a range of environmental assaults
  • Prebiotic Complex of Gluco-Oligosaccharides and Inulin helps to support your skin?s microbiome
  • Purified Deep-Sea Algae defends against pollution by forming a physical shield
  • Purified Mediterranean Brown Algae improves the skin barrier by supporting your skin?s calcium stores
  • Purified Knotgrass helps restore the damage often caused by infrared light
Tags: Night Serum, niod, survival 0

Name: Beauty Detox Shot - Liver Support
Short description: If you?ve tried every product on the market, but still battle with problematic skin ? perhaps you?re overlooking the liver.
Description:
If you?ve tried every product on the market, but still battle with problematic skin ? perhaps you?re overlooking the liver. A sluggish liver can mean a slow clearance of hormones from your body, which often leads to excess oil production from sebum producing cells. Then comes clogged and breakout prone skin, as well as feeling tired, bloated and even experiencing unbearable premenstrual syndrome. To help, this?Beauty Detox Shot?supports the normal function of your liver, to help promote a healthy complexion from the inside out. The formula contains liver-loving nutrients including Choline. It also blends traditional digestion supportive herbs such as Burdock Root and Globe Artichoke, along with antioxidant-rich Turmeric to enhance the detoxification process. Note this elixir has a bitter flavour which is intentional and designed to activate liver enzymes! Take your beauty detox shot with 30 mL of juice or 30 mls of your favourite smoothie to make it more palatable. Beauty Benefits Helping to improve your overall health and vitality from the inside out, this elixir stimulates the ability to clean toxic waste from your body and balance hormones. ? Botanical Actives
  • Altilix?
Traditionally, Artichoke leaves are used for the detoxification of the body and gastro-intestinal wellbeing. Altilix? is a powder extract of Globe Artichoke obtained from the leaves of a particular cultivar named?Cynara Cardunculus var. Bioactive compounds found in Artichoke leaves are shown to have a draining and detoxifying activity. Several clinical trials show how Artichoke extract helps improve symptoms of gastrointestinal disorders such as Irritable Bowel Syndrome and Dyspepsia.
  • Turmeric
Turmeric has been eaten traditionally as an anti-inflammatory and as a digestive aid. Curcumin, the main yellow compound found in turmeric, is a potent antioxidant.
  • Burdock Root
Burdock Root has been consumed traditionally as a tea to aid appetite and digestion, because it can stimulate the flow of digestive juices.?Preparations of Burdock Root?are often used for the relief of skin irritation and treatment of gastrointestinal complaints.
  • Choline
Choline is an essential vitamin required for the maintenance of normal liver function. While your?liver?can make small amounts, you must get the majority through your diet.?Choline works behind the scenes to maintain normal liver function through the role it plays in fat metabolism. Without adequate levels of free Choline, transportation of fat molecules out of your liver slows. This means, fat can begin to build up within your liver. As a result, your skin and complexion can be affected, as well as your overall health and vitality.
Tags: Detox Shot, Edible Beauty, Liver Support

Name: The Ordinary | Serum Foundation
Short description: Lightweight pigment suspension system with moderate coverage.
Description: Serum Foundation is a lightweight medium-coverage formulation available in 21 comprehensive shades. The foundation has a semi-matte finish that looks natural with a very lightweight serum feel. The shades are divided into three categories: 1 for fair to lighter tones, 2 for medium tones; and 3 for darker tones. Each category is then classified further by a second digit from 0 to 3 to indicate depth within each category. Finally, a letter is added to the shade code to identify the undertone: P (Pink) and R (Red) indicate cool undertones for lighter and darker shades respectively; N indicates a Neutral tone; Y indicates a Yellow undertone. View The Ordinary shade guide > The pigments used in this format are treated for a rich, highly-saturated effect. These pigments are suspended in our proprietary spreadability system that allows pigments to look natural on the skin, resist collecting within fine lines and stay on for longer. The foundations are compatible with most primers and are designed to work exceptionally well with the primers offering from The Ordinary. As with most liquid forms of foundation, it's ideal to shake the container lightly before use.

Name: In-Store Flu Vaccination
Short description: A flu vaccination is your very best defence against the common flu and is an important consideration to keep yourself and the people around you well during the winter months.\n\nVim & Co offers convenient by appointment vaccinations from our Northbridge store.
Description:
As we have seen with the current COVID-19 health crisis, it is important that we not only build up our own defences against illness but also protect those at high risk of severe complications within our community.  The influenza vaccine can help us as the single most important measure to prevent and reduce influenza infection. After vaccination, most adults develop antibody levels that are likely to protect them against the strains of virus represented in the vaccine.  In addition, there is likely to be protection against many related influenza variants. By choosing to vaccinate, we protect ourselves, prevent transmission to high-risk groups and potentially decrease the risk of hospitalisation. This will, in turn, ensure our hospitals are in the best place possible to treat patients experiencing severe illness from COVID-19 as the situation evolves. You can read more about the influenza vaccination, why it is recommended and how it can assist in protecting yourself and the broader community on our blog post here.  

BOOKINGS

  Vim & Co offers convenient by appointment vaccinations from our Northbridge store. Please note, all vaccinations are by appointment only - we are unable to offer walk-in vaccinations at this time. Please note: Some groups of people are eligible for free vaccines (see our blog post for a list of eligible groups) however free vaccines are only available through your local GP. Please note that whilst for these groups the vaccine is free, your GP may still charge a consult fee.   Time: Vaccination appointments are approximately 20 minutes  

Important information about your booking:

  You will be required to wait for 15 minutes INSIDE the pharmacy post-vaccination This is important to note for people who are currently self-isolating and for walk in appointments. If you are unable to wait, we are unable to administer the vaccination and it is recommended you seek vaccination from your local GP instead at a time convenient for you. If you are in mandatory isolation due to a suspected or confirmed case of COVID-19, you will not be able to attend your booking until all symptoms have subsided and you are cleared of the COVID-19 by your GP.   We are unable to vaccinate if you are experiencing any flu-like symptoms including sore throat and fever  Whilst you can technically have a flu vaccination whilst you have a cold, we are unable to vaccinate in store if symptoms are present given symptoms are similar to those experienced with COVID-19. If you are experiencing any symptoms and have a vaccination booked, simply call us to reschedule.   We are only able to vaccinate children over 10 years of age Children must be exactly 10 years of age or older  (EG. if your child is turning 10 in August, they can’t be vaccinated in a pharmacy until after their 10th birthday)
Tags: flu vaccination, pharmacy services

Products in this range include cough linctuses, lozenges and tablets, used to relieve dry and chesty coughs. The combinations of wet/chesty or dry/persistent coughs can be varied and onset can be due to a number of factors, ranging from simple to very complicated.   Coughs can be linked to underlying medical conditions so it's always important to make sure you speak to one of our Pharmacists to ensure the right product is recommended. Need a consult? We welcome the opportunity to provide one-on-one consults to discuss your health concerns. Consults allow us to undertake necessary screening to determine whether referral to other medical professionals is required, ensure the right products are recommended for you (with information on the correct and effective use of those products) and provide additional lifestyle and primary care advice to optimise your recovery and general health. Name: Fungal Infections
Short description: Vim & Co has a range of over the counter treatments available to manage fungal infections. Products in this range include creams, powders, sprays, foaming solutions, and shampoos.  For skin infections, often, using the wrong product on a rash can inadvertently make the rash worse so it is important to ensure that your rash is correctly identified before commencing any treatments. Some antifungals are combined with other ingredients like hydrocortisone to increase their effectiveness so there are a few variations and options that our Pharmacists can go through with you. For fungal nail infections, our over the counter treatments are used in more severe nail infections where it has penetrated deep into the nail bed. The treatment is extensive and only needs to be used once a week. Our Pharmacists can ensure that your condition is correctly identified (as many skin and nail conditions can look similar!) and recommend the best antifungal product for your specific symptoms.   Need a consult? Name: Cold and Flu
Short description:
Vim & Co has a range of over the counter products available to treat common cold and flu symptoms.
Products in this range include day and night cold and flu tablets, nasal sprays, throat lozenges, throat gargles and sprays and immune boosters.
Cold and flu tablets contain either pseudoephedrine or phenylephrine as a primary decongestant to unblock stuffy noses or sinuses and clear the foggy, heavy-headed feeling that comes with a cold.
They will usually also have paracetamol to help with pain or fever. The night time component usually contains an antihistamine ingredient that helps to dry up a runny nose and to cause drowsiness, to aid in sleep.
Some cold and flu tablets may or may not contain an ingredient for cough and it's usually an ingredient for a dry cough rather than a wet/chesty cough.
Along with many variations of cold and flu tablets- for day, night or both, with and without an ingredient for cough - comes a whole range of other products that help with the symptoms of a cold, like sore throat and fever. There are also natural health options that may help to boost the body's natural immune system and these can be used in conjunction with traditional medicines that are available over the counter.
Why should I talk to the pharmacist?
Oral decongestants are not suitable for patients with high uncontrolled blood pressure and those on other medications. Our Pharmacist can recommend safe alternative options based on your current medical conditions and other medications you are taking.
Need a consult? We welcome the opportunity to provide one-on-one consults to discuss your health concerns. Consults allow us to undertake necessary screening to determine whether referral to other medical professionals is required, ensure the right products are recommended for you (with information on the correct and effective use of those products) and provide additional lifestyle and primary care advice to optimise your recovery and general health. The Shakti Acupressure Pillow is a pillow with spikes distributed on it, that unlock the benefits of acupressure to relax your body and ease your mind, in the comfort of your own home. It is designed with a half-moon curve to fit perfectly under your neck, lower back, feet or legs. The pillow can also be applied underneath the hamstrings, calves and thighs to assist with healthy recovery post-workout, as well as against a couch or chair at your desk, for lumbar support.   • Healthy circulation
  • Relaxation of tense muscles
  • Soothing of headaches
  • Relief from stress
  • Relaxed body and mind
  • General vitality
  • Deep, restful sleep

15 minutes is all you need to put the acupressure to work on your tension-heavy areas.

Tags: candles, Chandelles, gifts, mini candles, Plant based
Meta: ingredients: 100% plant based stearin wax (RSPO certified) with cotton wick
Meta: how_to:
COMPOSITION AND CARE

Due to the nature of the wax, our candles may produce a soft white film on the outside. This is known as blooming, and is a naturally occurring process. It in no way affects the quality or burning of the candle and can be removed with a soft cloth gently

Keep away from draughts and do not move the candle once lit

Keep out of reach from children and pets

Don't leave it burning without supervision. Blow out candle before flame reaches 2cm from base.

Always lit in a well ventilated space and not flammable surface. Not suitable for outdoor use.

Cut the top of the wick approx 5mm before burning. Do not burn more than 2 hours at a time

Name: Waterless Pure Essential Oil Diffuser
Short description: The Waterless Pure Essential Oil Diffuser allows users to experience the purity and uncompromised quality of In Essence Pure Essential Oils straight from the source, directly from the bottle.
Description:
Just like the name, this Waterless Pure Essential Oil Diffuser allows you to experience the purity and uncompromised quality of In Essence Pure Essential Oils directly from the bottle. Unlike any conventional diffusers, the Waterless Essential Oil Diffuser adopts the latest technology to release a fine cool mist composed entirely of pure essential oils without the need for heat or water, which results in a much stronger aroma dispersed throughout the air. The undiluted essential oil particles will calm the mind, give you better sleep, and uplift your mind and body. With its cordless and compact design operated with portable battery-operated unit, your can conveniently experience the benefits of aromatherapy around the home, at work or in the car without hassle. What makes In Essence Waterless Pure Essential Oil Diffuser Special?
  • Concentrated Pure Essential Oil Therapy
  • Air Purifier
  • No Heat, No Water
  • Wireless Portability
  • Chargeable Battery
  • USB Power Cord
  • 10-30 hours run time
  • 3 Timer Settings (30/60/90 mins)
  • Intermittent Mist Release
  • Safe Auto Shut Off
Old & New Version
  • Old: Only the diffuser
  • New: The diffuser + IE: Breathe Essential Oil 10ml (Uplifting blend of Eucalyptus, Mint, and Pine to relieve symptoms of cold, flu, sinusitis, mild respiratory infection, mucus congestion, and headache)
NOTE: Compatible with essential oil bottles no larger than 10mL. Not all essential oil bottles may be suitable. Complete your In Essence essential oils with the other scents here. *To get more updates about our products, follow us on Facebook or Instagram.
Tags: essential oils, gifts, Wellness
Meta: how_to:
Instructions for Use:

1. Remove the nozzle by pushing upright through the hole in the base of the diffuser. Attach your In Essence Pure Essential Oil into the nozzle (bottles sizes up to 20mL Compatible). Secure nozzle back into the diffuser, ensuring the marked arrows are aligned (avoid chemical, synthetic oils as these will cause the diffuser to malfunction).

2. Hold the POWER button to turn on the diffuser. This will activate Intermittent mist dispersion. Intermittent mist intervals can be adjusted by further pressing the power button. 1st Press: On 10sec, Off 60sec, Repeat. 2nd Press: On 20sec, Off 60sec, Repeat. 3rd Press: On 30sec, Off 60sec, Repeat. 3. Press TIMER to activate the timer mode (30/60/90 mins). To turn off the diffuser at any time, hold the POWER button.

NOTE: Compatible with essential oil bottles no larger than 20mL. Not all essential oil bottles may be suitable. For full instructions refer to the manual enclosed. Responsible use of Essential Oils Adults Only. Not to be taken. Keep out of reach of children

Each book features curved corners for safety, bright colourful illustrations and children can work their fine motor skills through the engaging sound buttons. Wonderfully sturdy, these board books can be read over and over again providing easy to turn pages for little hands.

Please note this product contains button batteries (secured inside the battery compartment with a screw). Button batteries are unsafe if swallowed. For information about button battery safety please click here.

Name: KIDDIE CONNECT Abc (lowercase) Chunky and Tracing Puzzle
Description:
Kiddie Connect is all about children connecting with their imaginations and sense of fun.

A useful puzzle for helping children to become familiar with the alphabet, and with the role of letters in the formation of words.  A tracing stick is provided to help build the fine motor skills, practice pen holding and the correct way to write each letter. A great preschool puzzle to prepare a little one on the movements of writing and build their muscles ready for writing for extended periods of time. 

Ideas for enhancing play and learning:
  • Ask the child to select the letter that his/her name starts with.  Repeat this with other family members and pets.
  • While placing letters in their correct position on the board, it could be useful for the child to learn the sound of the letter and to have him/her think of other words that begin with this same sound.
  • Ask your child to maze through the apple from 1 -10
  • First simple naming words can be formed with the accompanying use of the Uppercase Puzzle. Children can begin to recognise the difference between upper and lowercase letters.
  • Trace and practice the movement of writing letters. 

Features:
  • Suitable for ages: 18+ months 
  • Crafted from wood

Dimensions: 28cm (l) 28cm (w) 3cm (h)

Name: KIDDIE CONNECT 123 Carrot Puzzle
Description:
A colourful and playful educational puzzle which captures the attention of preschoolers. It encourages the development of colour and number identification and also assists with hand eye-coordination. Match the number dots to the numbers on the colourful carrots or match the carrot colours to the colour on the board. 

This gorgeous puzzle makes a lovely Easter gift. 

Promote and enhance learning by:

  • Asking the child to identify the colours of the carrots and to match them with the colours on the puzzle board
  • Ask the child to feed a certain number carrot to the bunny
  • Asking the child to name the numbers on the carrots as they are being placed into the corresponding numbers on the board and then count from 1 to 10 aloud.
  • Discuss the bunny, what do bunny rabbits eat? Where do they live?

Suitable for ages: 18+ months

Name: KIDDIE CONNECT Flying Balloon Chunky Shape Puzzle
Description:
An educational puzzle that promotes shape and colour recognition and development of the grasping and holding fine motor skill in young children of three years and younger.

Enhance play and learning by:

  • Asking the child to name the colours of the balloons as they are placed onto the board
  • Asking the child to name the shapes of each balloon.  What other things do you know of that have this shape?
  • Introducing concepts of “flying” in the sky – what other things can fly?

Ages 18+ Months

It offers opportunity to develop: 

  • problem solving skills

  • fine motor skills involving placing and balancing.

The animals also provide the opportunity for story telling and open ended play.

Name: Deep Collagen (UNFLAVOURED) 150G
Short description: A  marine collagen containing supplement  with probiotic and superfood ingredients aim to support skin elasticity and and hydration for overall better skin health.\n\n
Description:
100% clean, certified sustainable marine collagen peptides that contribute to skin elasticity, hydration, collagen density and protection deep within the skin. This fine powder also contains Bioavailability Factors™—the digestive enzyme bromelain and our exclusive probiotic strain, Lactobacillus rhamnosus GUT5Y™—for enhanced absorption.

Available in Berry and Unflavoured, DEEP COLLAGEN™ contains hydrolysed marine collagen that is sourced from wild-caught, deep-sea North Atlantic cod, exclusively and sustainably sourced in accordance with stringent Marine Stewardship Council (MSC) standards.

The most abundant protein in our bodies, collagen is essential for plump, firm skin. As we age, our body’s ability to produce collagen proteins naturally declines, leading to fine lines, wrinkles and loss of moisture. Hydrolysed marine collagen contributes to skin elasticity and hydration, supporting healthy collagen density and helping to protect collagen deep within the skin.

Good to know: non GMO, no artificial flavours, preservatives or colours, no added gluten, dairy, soy, or eggs. Contains fish.
Tags: cruelty free, vegan
Meta: ingredients: Unflavoured: MSC-certified sustainable marine collagen (99.3%), bromelain derived from pineapple (0.64%), Lactobacillus rhamnosus GUT5Y™ (0.02%).
Meta: how_to:
Mix 1 ½ tsp (3g) of The Beauty Chef marine collagen powder into 150mL of water, your favourite drink or a smoothie and consume immediately. 
DEEP COLLAGEN™ can be enjoyed up to 3 times per day in chilled or room temperature beverages or food and can be taken with any other Beauty Chef product. Storage: Store below 25°C, away from sunlight in a cool, dry place. Always use a dry spoon and consume within 8 weeks of opening.
